{
    "name": "Fried Empanadas",
    "instructions": "1. Prepare the dough by mixing flour and salt, cutting in shortening, and adding water until a dough forms. Wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour.\n\n2. Meanwhile, make the filling by sautéing onions in olive oil, then adding ground beef, paprika, cumin, pepper, and salt. Cook until beef is browned, then stir in raisins and vinegar. Refrigerate for 1 hour.\n\n3. Roll the dough and portion it into small balls. Flatten each ball, fill with beef mixture, and fold into a half-moon shape, sealing the edges.\n\n4. Fry the empanadas in hot oil until browned, about 2.5 minutes per side. Drain on paper towels and serve hot.",
